courses.notes: This is the first semester of a two-semester project.  The second semester, which will be offered in January 2018, will involve interviewing Holocaust survivors.  In September 2017, students will submit a Criminal Records Check, have a screening interview, and submit a short essay explaining why they want to take the course.  Details will be provided on the first day of class.Students will receive credit for either HIST 1195, section 001 or ENGL 2237, section 001 and not both courses. Students should register in ENGL 2237.For further information, please contact Rachel Mines or Kina Cavicchioli at rmines@langara.ca or kcavicchioli@langara.ca.

courses.subject: ENGL
courses.title: Exploring Literature
courses.notes: The Robots Are Coming!This course (ENGL 2237 Sec 002) will investigate the notion of artificial intelligence and how writers have explored philosophical questions about humanity through robot and android characters. We will view films and read a variety of short stories, poems, novellas, and novels, along with an assortment of critical articles—including work by Alan Turing, the founder of theoretical computer science—that explore the line between human and machine, and the implications of defining such a line in the presence of advanced A.I. Are robots capable of exhibiting emotions or creativity? Is artificial intelligence entitled to basic civil rights? Is there a danger that robots will destroy humanity? Should we even build intelligent machines?
